

```sql
CAST(expression AS target_type)
```

---

### ðŸ”§ Common Examples

| Purpose | Example | Result |
|--------|---------|--------|
| String â†’ Integer | `CAST('123' AS UNSIGNED)` | `123` |
| Integer â†’ String | `CAST(123 AS CHAR)` | `'123'` |
| Float â†’ Integer | `CAST(123.45 AS SIGNED)` | `123` |
| Date â†’ String | `CAST(CURDATE() AS CHAR)` | `'2025-09-22'` |
| String â†’ Date | `CAST('2025-09-22' AS DATE)` | `2025-09-22` |

---

### ðŸ§ª Use in Queries

```sql
SELECT student_id, CAST(course_progress AS CHAR) AS progress_text
FROM student_info;
```

> âœ… Converts `course_progress` to string for display or export.

---

### ðŸ”„ Related: `CONVERT()` (MySQL Alternative)

```sql
SELECT CONVERT('123.45', DECIMAL(5,2));
```

> âœ… Works similarly to `CAST()`, but with slightly different syntax.

